*Description*

We currently have a minimum limit to not display any plans below 88 calories. This means that once we add new skus for 60 kcal we need to update this limit to 54 in order to render the correct options on all plans pages. Once we do this change we would also need to tweak our rounding logic for the 60kcal and 100kcal plans in order to maintain our current behavior;

BAU: With the 88 minimum kcal limit in place the behavior to display plans works like this;

87 <  = *no plans*
88 - 149 = *fresh + dry 100 kcal plans*
and so on‚Ä¶

Once the limit is updated to 54 kcal the logic the behavior to display plans works like this;

53 < = *no plans*
54 - 80 = *dry 60 kcal plan*
81 - 149 = *fresh + dry 100 kcal plans*
and so on..

We want to maintain the range of where we assign users to a 100 kcal plan which means that we (BE üòÑ ) need to tweak this so that the behavior with the new minimum kcal limit of 54 in place works like this;

53 < = *no plans*
54 - 87 = *dry 60 kcal plan*
88 - 149 = *fresh + dry 100 kcal plans (BAU)*
and so on..

{panel}

